rComments: Lots of readings, a lot of assignments too but most were not too heavy so you definitely have time to get it all done, you have a lot of opportunities for make-up assignments if you are trying to improve your mark. As a required course for the religion program, it was fairly interesting, I would recommend it if you're considering a religion minor.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Professor Harris managed to interest me (an atheist) in course material entirely centred around Christ (in a course I was required to take). She's witty, insightful and engaging. It's worth noting that she has high expectations, but she's more than happy to go out of her way to help her students succeed. You will work, and it will be worth it.

I loved this class and she is an articulate, amusing and presents her lectures well.  There are many assignments and mountains of reading.  Many found her grading harsh, but I got better grades from her than from Jason the TA. Get to grips with the first couple of readings and the scene by scene analysis of music videos for the summaries and exam.
workload is way too heavy. many assignments and are marked quite harshly. final paper worth only 20% but was required to write up to 10 pages. Final exam was not optional like the previous year.

reading materials & lectures are thoughtful but the workload is too heavy. reading materials are very lengthy. can go up to 100 pages a week. There are assignments throughout the semester, which can include an optional final paper of 8-10 pages and a number of reports. There is also a final exam. Class average is low.

Prof Harris gives extremely well-organized lectures and her lecture slides are well detailed. I thoroughly enjoyed this course as it was very fun, thought-provoking and interesting. However, she is a hard marker! Be prepared to do lots of readings (and a close one at that)! She is overall a very knowledgeable, kind and funny professor.
Probably one of the best female professors I've had at UofT. Very intelligent and has a great sense of humour.
Prof. Harris is amazing! Attending her class was relaxing - she's such a positive and pleasant person, and a great instructor. Recommended!
No Comments

she is an affective university professor who knows her material well and shows much interest in the subject. although i realized that it was not the course for me during the semester i looked forward to attending her class because it was very interactive and i appreciated her lectures.
Best teacher at this school.  Extremely helpful, enjoyable to learn from.  If you didn't like this teacher it is because you didn't work hard and you did poorly in her class.  You snooze you lose.

I found the professor very unclear, and not helpful in understanding the topic.  Her disucssions weren't controled and flew all over the place.  Further, course expectations were unclear and comments were not helpful. Good passion for the material but poor teaching ability.

A professor who is passionate about teaching and actually cares about her students (and knows all their names!). Her infectious enthusiasm stands in stark contrast to the other egotistical prof's I have had who don't care about thier students, or about presenting material in an engaging, exciting manner.
Actually makes religion interesting! The material is made accessible and she gets the class engaged through group discussion and utilizing various mediums such as film and music.

Prof. Harris is an amazing prof. She is brilliant, and clear, and ALWAYS willing to help her students. She took every opportunity to make sure we felt comfortable with where we were in the course, but she never spoon fed. She is more than fair, and always willing to listen. She never patronizes. She never dismisses. She is an incredible professor.

GREAT professor.  She brought in alot of interesting forms of popular culture and was able to engage the classroom.  Very helpful and considerate to science students as well :) She really likes class discussion
Prof. Harris was great! She knows her stuff and is enthusiastic about it!  It was always interesting to listen to her and all her insights! :)
simply amazing. she makes even the most dry of material come to life.

Had her as my TA for HIS220.  Amazingly supportive and engaged instructor!  Very challenging marker but gives lots of suggestions and assistance with your writing! None of that 'satisfactory- needs improvement' b.s.! One of the best young prof. at SMC!

This is one of the best courses I've taken at UofT. Its only downfall is that Prof Harris is a very hard marker. However, it's the kind of class where you won't mind putting in the extra effort necessary, and Prof Harris herself is extremely helpful and kind.
Challenging class taught by an excellent professor. One of the most caring teachers I've ever encountered.
No Comments

Professor Harris is fantastic.Her selection of course readings were extremely interesting as were class discussions.It's no exaggeration to say that this was a course whose merits were more than academic;it was personally and spiritually rewarding.

One of the absolute BEST courses I have ever taken at the university. Harris is brilliant, her lectures are fasciniating and she is one of the nicest people you will ever meet. You are nuts if you don't take this course.
Awesome Professor!  Always willing to help out, humourous and simply inspiring.
Helpful, Insightful, a wellspring of knowledge, a wonderful professor
